</h3><p class="sc-iLLNPL dGtRC pf-107_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">This course ensures volunteers understand and promote equality, embrace diversity, and uphold human rights within their roles, creating an inclusive environment for all service users.
</p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-bhqpXc bptxD pf-109_ pf-heading-1-h3">Preventing radicalisation for volunteers
</h3><p class="sc-iLLNPL dGtRC pf-111_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Teaches volunteers about the risks associated with radicalisation and provides them with the skills to identify signs of radicalisation and understand the steps to help prevent it.
</p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-bhqpXc bptxD pf-113_ pf-heading-1-h3">Data security awareness for volunteers
</h3><p class="sc-iLLNPL dGtRC pf-115_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">This course is crucial for volunteers handling sensitive information in this digital age. It covers data protection principles and secure data handling practices to comply with legal standards like GDPR.
</p></div></div></div><div class="sc-hzhKNl fltMam pf-117_ pf-r pf-c-cm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:6;--c-md:6;--c-lg:6"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-djTQOc gLxCly pf-118_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-bhqpXc bptxD pf-119_ pf-heading-1-h3">Safeguarding children for volunteers
</h3><p class="sc-iLLNPL dGtRC pf-121_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Similar to safeguarding adults, this course focuses on protecting children. Volunteers learn about the types of abuse, signs of abuse in children, and appropriate measures to take if child abuse is suspected.
</p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-bhqpXc bptxD pf-123_ pf-heading-1-h3">Emergency first aid at work (EFAW) - Level 3
</h3><p class="sc-iLLNPL dGtRC pf-125_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">It is an intensive course that equips volunteers with the skills to handle emergencies, provide first aid, and potentially save lives in critical moments.
</p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-bhqpXc bptxD pf-127_ pf-heading-1-h3">Basic life support (Adult resuscitation) - Level 2
</h3><p class="sc-iLLNPL dGtRC pf-129_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Volunteers are trained in basic life support techniques for adults, including CPR, essential skills in emergencies where medical response might be delayed.
